# 📘 Convert HTML to Excel – Prompt-Based Automation Agent

## 🚀 Overview

This project is a **prompt-driven automation system** that:

* 📦 Reads LRE ZIP reports
* 📂 Extracts and processes them
* 📊 Converts HTML/CSV data into Excel
* 📈 Compares multiple reports with trend analysis
* 📧 Sends reports via Outlook email

All actions are controlled using **natural language prompts**.

---

# 🧱 Project Architecture

```
User Prompt → FastAPI → LLaMA (optional parsing) → Python Engine → Output (Excel / Email)
```

---

# 📦 Dependencies & Installation

## 🔧 Required Python Packages

Install using:

```bash
pip install fastapi uvicorn pandas beautifulsoup4 lxml pywin32
```

---

## 📚 Dependency Details

| Library          | Purpose                              |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `fastapi`        | API framework                        |
| `uvicorn`        | ASGI server to run FastAPI           |
| `pandas`         | Data processing & Excel generation   |
| `beautifulsoup4` | HTML parsing                         |
| `lxml`           | Faster HTML/XML parser               |
| `pywin32`        | Outlook email automation             |
| `zipfile`        | Extract ZIP files (built-in)         |
| `os`             | File system handling (built-in)      |
| `re`             | Regex for parsing prompts (built-in) |

